            . On the 25th of February the prisoner brought this bridle (producing it.) to me to sell; I stopped it on suspicion, and advertised it; Mr. Spencer came and I delivered it to him.</p>
               <p>Breakspear. I am sure it is my master's property; it came home the 20th or 21st of February.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was coming from the country and met with a man coming up, and he asked me to buy this<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177304210054"></xptr> bridle; I bought it for 9 d. when I came to London I went to sell it, and the gentleman stopped it.</p>
